.\CHANGELOG.md:11:- **Switched procedural Star Wars building bundle material shader from Built-in `Standard` to URP `Universal Render Pipeline/Lit`** with fallback to `Universal Render Pipeline/Simple Lit` during assetbundle build, and switched tinting to `SetColor("_BaseColor", tint)` to keep `Hybrid Renderer V2` SRP batching compatibility.
.\CHANGELOG.md:12:- Rebuilt all 12 Star Wars building bundles on branch `feat/sw-building-bundles-20260531` using headless `Unity 2021.3.45f1` from `scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder` and confirmed the build log includes `Universal Render Pipeline/Lit`.
.\CHANGELOG.md:15:- **12 remaining Star Wars BUILDING bundles were 90-byte stubs** — `sw-assembly-line`, `sw-blast-wall`, `sw-durasteel-barrier`, `sw-guard-tower`, `sw-heavy-foundry`, `sw-mining-facility`, `sw-processing-plant`, `sw-skyshield-generator`, `sw-tech-union-lab`, `sw-tibanna-refinery`, `sw-vulture-nest`, `sw-weapons-factory`. As placeholders they kept those buildings native in-game and made the swap engine (#986) re-load a useless stub every frame, flooding the AssetSwap log with "another AssetBundle with the same files is already loaded". Built REAL Unity 2021.3.45f1 AssetBundles for all 12 (each ~46-47 KB, up from 90 B) — distinct procedural SW-styled building silhouettes (factory / wall / tower / refinery / mine / lab / shield-emitter / vulture-nest / blast-barrier) on a faction-tinted Standard material (CIS grey / Republic white). New self-contained Editor builder `BuildSwBuildingBundles.cs` (meshes generated in-C# via `CombineInstance` of box primitives — no Blender / glTF dependency), promoted to `scripts/unity/unity-assetbundle-builder/Assets/Editor/`. Built headless with the canonical `Unity.exe 2021.3.45f1` (`-batchmode -nographics -quit -executeMethod BuildSwBuildingBundles.Build`), exit 0, bundle headers verified `UnityFS ... 2021.3.45f1`. Bundle filename == `visual_asset` key == Addressable key; all 12 keys were already present in `addressables.yaml` / `asset_pipeline.yaml` (no CRC/hash fields, so no registration change needed). NOT deployed — deploy happens at reconcile.
.\CHANGELOG.md:106:- **Real meshes + AssetBundles for 19 previously-stub Star Wars units (#964 / #946 fallback).** Replaced 896/1092-byte stub `model.glb` (and absent meshes) with Blender-generated clean-room parametric silhouettes (walkers, fighters, hovertanks, spider/tripod droids, troopers, gunship), converted to FBX and built into Unity 2021.3.45f1 AssetBundles (filename = `visual_asset` = Addressable key). Covers marquee gaps: `sw-general-grievous`, `sw-rep-at-te-walker`, `sw-tri-fighter`, `sw-aat-walker`/`sw-cis-aat`, `sw-v19-torrent`, `sw-jedi-knight`, `sw-cis-spider-droid`, `sw-rep-laat-gunship`, `sw-droideka`, plus arc/commando/sniper/magna-guard/medical/b1-squad/wall-guard/stap/barc. Bundles are 82–153 KB real geometry (not 90-byte stubs); render-proofs in `docs/screenshots/model-previews/sw-procedural/`. Acquisition strategy (Sketchfab token path, BF2/Frostbite extraction steps, OSS/CC0 sources, legal posture) documented in `docs/sessions/sw-asset-acquisition-20260530.md`. New tooling: `unity-assetbundle-builder/generate_sw_procedural.py`, `render_proof.py`, `Assets/Editor/BuildSwMissingBundles.cs`. Placeholder-grade — meant to be upgraded by higher-fidelity Sketchfab/BF2 sources when the user supplies a token or runs the extractor.
.\CHANGELOG.md:127:  - **`GraphicsMaterialUpgrader` (`src/Runtime/Graphics/GraphicsMaterialUpgrader.cs`)** — `Upgrade(Material, assetKey)` produces a new `Universal Render Pipeline/Lit` material that carries over the base albedo map + tint and layers in declared PBR maps (albedo `_BaseMap`, metallic+gloss `_MetallicGlossMap`, normal `_BumpMap`, AO `_OcclusionMap`, emission `_EmissionMap`) with the matching shader keywords (`_METALLICSPECGLOSSMAP` / `_NORMALMAP` / `_OCCLUSIONMAP` / `_EMISSION`). Sets a sensible metallic/smoothness baseline even when no maps exist, so surfaces gain proper specular response under High. Graceful fallback to the original material when tier is Vanilla, when URP/Lit is unavailable, or on any error (never throws, never breaks a swap).
.\CHANGELOG.md:182:- **Star Wars bundles shipped primitive-placeholder prefabs instead of real meshes (#101/#947)** — The shipped `warfare-starwars` AssetBundles wired 64/75 bundle prefabs to Unity built-in primitive meshes (Cube/Capsule/Sphere, `fileID:10202`), so even a perfect in-game Harmony swap rendered cubes. Root cause: `*.fbx`/`*.glb`/`*.obj` are gitignored, so in a fresh worktree the only committed mesh source is `packs/warfare-starwars/assets/raw/<asset_id>/model.glb` (the `!packs/*/assets/raw/*/model.glb` allowlist); the intended pipeline (`convert_models.py` Blender GLB→FBX → `GenerateStarWarsPrefabsFromModels` → `BuildAssetBundles`) was never reproduced end-to-end in the worktree, and the primitive-only generators (`GenerateStarWarsPrefabs.cs`/`BuildAll.cs`, which *skip existing* prefabs) had poisoned the prefab dir. Fixes:
.\CHANGELOG.md:186:  - Rebuilt the AssetBundles and updated the 3 newly-real bundles in `packs/warfare-starwars/assets/bundles/`: `sw-cis-spider-droid` 43,768B→1,467,170B, `sw-rep-clone-commander` 44,382B→207,814B, `sw-rep-at-te-walker` 44,197B→96,885B (the other 11 real-mesh bundles were already real). Bundle-mesh content externally verified by loading the rebuilt bundles back in Unity (`VerifyBundleMesh`): spider-droid maxVerts=48,515, clone-commander 8 meshes maxVerts=1,751, at-te-walker 36 meshes, droideka maxVerts=65,541 — vs the primitive control `sw-rep-clone-pilot` at a single 550-vert capsule. Deployed to the live game pack and verified by SHA-256 match.
.\CHANGELOG.md:2234:- **AssetSwapSystem prefab extraction** — `TrySwapRenderMeshFromBundle` now falls back to loading a `GameObject` from the bundle and extracting `Mesh`/`Material` via `MeshFilter`/`MeshRenderer`/`SkinnedMeshRenderer` when direct `LoadAsset<Mesh>` returns null; Unity AssetBundles built from prefabs (all warfare-starwars bundles) previously caused every swap to silently return false
.\CHANGELOG.md:2314:- **AssetSwapSystem prefab extraction** — `TrySwapRenderMeshFromBundle` now falls back to loading a `GameObject` from the bundle and extracting `Mesh`/`Material` via `MeshFilter`/`MeshRenderer`/`SkinnedMeshRenderer` when direct `LoadAsset<Mesh>` returns null; Unity AssetBundles built from prefabs (all warfare-starwars bundles) previously caused every swap to silently return false; `SkinnedMeshRenderer` now preferred over static renderers to keep mesh+material paired from the same component
.\CHANGELOG.md:2345:- **Star Wars asset bundles** — built Unity AssetBundles for 25 warfare-starwars pack units/buildings (CIS + Republic); prefab sources added to `unity-assetbundle-builder/Assets/Prefabs/`
.\CHANGELOG.md:2351:- **Star Wars vanilla bundles** — removed 42 primitive placeholder AssetBundles; units now fall back to vanilla DINO visuals until real assets are imported
.\CHANGELOG.md:2790:- Unity AssetBundles and prefab GUIDs synchronized after Unity project rebuild
.\CHANGELOG.md:2796:- **Unity AssetBundles** — 75 colored primitive placeholder bundles (StandaloneWindows64) for all 50 warfare-starwars visual_asset keys; Republic units are white+blue, CIS units are grey, special units (Jedi Knight, General Grievous) have distinct colors
